A '''case presentation''' is a formal communication between [[health care professional]]s (doctors, pharmacists, nurses, therapists, nutritionist etc.) regarding a patient's clinical information. Essential parts of a case presentation include: * Identification * Reason for consultation/admission * Chief complaints (CC) - what made patients seek medical attention. * History of present illness (HPI) - circumstances relating to chief complaints. * Past medical history (PMHx) * Past surgical history * Current medications * [[Allergies]] * Family history (FHx) * Social history (SocHx) * [[Physical examination]] (PE) * [[Laboratory results]] (Lab) * Other investigations ([[Medical imaging|imaging]], [[biopsy]] etc.) * Case summary and impression * [[Management plans]] * follow up in clinic or hospital * Adherence of the patient to treatment * success of the treatment or failure. * causes of success or failure.
