{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2018}} {{Use Indian English|date=March 2018}} '''Harpal Singh Tiwana''' (born 8 August 1935 in District Ludhiana Punjab) was one of the most prominent [[Punjabi people|Punjabi]] playwrights of all time. <ref name="TOI">{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2003-06-28/news-interviews/27185270_1_theatre-personality-om-puri-harpal-tiwana|title=Om Puri pays tribute to stage actor|date=28 June 2003|publisher=Times of India|accessdate=2009-03-31}}</ref>
His two ventures into film making ''[[Long Da Lishkara]]'' and ''[[Diva bale Sari Raat]]'' became landmarks in [[Punjabi cinema]]. He also directed two television productions – ''Sanjhi Deewar'' and an unfinished project on ''Maharaja Ranjit singh''.
His famous plays include ''Sirhind di Deewar''.<ref>http://fatehgarhsahib.nic.in/Sir_deewar.htm</ref> He established ''Punjab Kala Manch'' at [[Patiala]] along with his wife to promote local artists.<ref>http://www.rediff.com/entertai/apr/04puri.htm</ref> Both Tiwana and his wife Neena Tiwana are graduates from [[National School of Drama]].<ref>http://www.ludhianadistrict.com/personality/nirmal-rishi.php</ref> Neena Tiwana and his son Manpal Tiwana are also playing a key role in promoting the theatre in [[Punjab (India)|Punjab]].
Harpal died in a road accident near [[Palampur]] in [[Himachal Pradesh]], on 19 May 2002, was cremated at Badungar cremation ground at [[Patiala]].<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.accessmylibrary.com/coms2/summary_0286-25621196_ITM | work=Asia Africa Intelligence Wire | title=Tiwana cremated | date=22 May 2002}}</ref>
''Harpal Tiwana Foundation''<ref>http://www.tribuneindia.com/2007/20070506/cth1.htm</ref> was set up in the memory of great Punjabi theater personality<ref>http://cities.expressindia.com/fullstory.php?newsid=107930</ref> after his death.
