==Phonology==
{{Main|Irish phonology}}

A notable feature of Irish phonology is that consonants (except {{IPA|/h/}}) come in pairs, one "broad" ([[velarization|velarized]], pronounced with the back of the tongue pulled back towards the soft palate) and one "slender" ([[Palatalization (phonetics)|palatalized]], pronounced with the middle of the tongue pushed up towards the hard palate).

