{{autobiography|date=September 2014}}
'''Lola Koundakjian'''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lolakoundakjian.com/ftp___lolakoundakjian.com/Welcome.html |title=Lola Koundakjian’s official website |author=Lola Koundakjian |publisher= |date=November 2014 |accessdate=27 Nov 2014}}</ref> was born in [[Beirut]], [[Lebanon]] and has resided in [[New York City]] since 1979. She writes in Armenian, her [[native language|mother tongue]], and [[English language|English]]. She has organized evenings dedicated to the Dead Armenian Poets Society since she was in university, and has [[curator|curated]] the online Armenian Poetry Project since 2006.
A regular reader in New York City and its tri-state area, Koundakjian has appeared in four international poetry festivals: at [[Medellin, Colombia|Medellin]], [[Colombia]], 2010; <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.festivaldepoesiademedellin.org/es/Revista/ultimas_ediciones/86_87/koundakjian.html |title=Lola Koundakjian, Armenia |author= |publisher=Corporación de Arte y Poesía Prometeo |date=November 2014 |accessdate=27 Nov 2014}}</ref> Lima, Peru, 2013;<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fiplima.com/2013/poetas/armenia.html |title=FIP Lima 2013 |author= |publisher=FIPLIMA |date=3 Jul 2013 |accessdate=27 Nov 2014}}</ref> [[Ramallah]], [[West Bank]], 2013; and [[Trois-Rivières]], [[Quebec]], [[Canada]], 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fiptr.com/poete_bio-2014.html |title=Biographies |author= |publisher=Québecor |date=10 Oct 2014 |accessdate=27 Nov 2014}}</ref> Her [[translation]]s of modern [[Istanbul]] [[poet]]s have been included in [[Western Armenian]] [[Armenian language|language]] teaching manuals.
Lola has received two grants from the Northern Manhattan Arts Alliance, New York, USA, and the Naji Naaman Literary Prize in Lebanon. She is the author of the Armenian/English poetry collection ''The Accidental Observer'',<ref>[https://www.amazon.com/Accidental-Observer-R-H-Lola-Koundakjian/dp/0578066181/ref=la_B004Z57VO4_1_1?s=books&ie=UTF8&qid=1411383824&sr=1-1]</ref> which includes [[translation]]s in [[Spanish language|Spanish]].
Koundakjian's second book, ''Advice To A Poet'', was a finalist in Armenia's Orange Book Prize in 2012 and was published in 2015 by Amotape Libros in [[Lima, Peru|Lima]], [[Peru]].
